I"õ<p>There are two ways to purchase an Amazon Gift Card:
    1. In a physical form a local store,
    1. Purchasing a digital gift card from the Amazon web store.</p>

<p>For information on local stores where Amazon Gift Cards may be published, see the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/b/?node=13582391011" target="_blank"><strong>Amazon Gift Card</strong></a> website.</p>

<h2 id="buying-a-digital-amazon-gift-card">Buying a digital Amazon Gift Card</h2>

<p>There are two paths to purchasing an Amazon Gift Card:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Visit the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gift-cards/b?ie=UTF8&amp;node=2238192011" target="_blank"><strong>Amazon Gift Card Hub</strong></a>.<br />
 <img src="gifthub-1.png" alt="Amazon Gift Card Hub" />
    <ol>
      <li>There are three options of delivery methods: eGift, ‚ÄúPrint at Home,‚Äù and ‚ÄúMail.‚Äù Choose the method that is best for you. In this example, follow <strong>Step 2</strong> for the eGift Delivert method. The other methods are require a printer or a mailing address, respectively.</li>
      <li>This section allows you to select by occasion. This is purely a cosmetic choice.</li>
      <li>This section allows you to purchase a gift to from third-party source, such as Apple gift cards for your Apple account, Visa cards, and Starbucks gift cards.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>Buying an <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Amazon-Amazon-com-eGift-Cards/dp/BT00DC6QU4"><strong>Amazon.com eGift Card</strong></a>.<br />
 <img src="giftcard-purchase.png" alt="The Purchase Details Screen for an Amazon Gift Card" />
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Card Designs</strong> - This is a purely cosmetic step for the digital Amazon Gift Card. This has no bearing on the product.</li>
      <li><strong>Amount</strong> - Select from a pre-filled amount, or enter a custom value.
        <blockquote>
          <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> The amount specified here must be greater than $1 (USD).<br />
 <img src="min-val.png" alt="A minimum value warning displays for any values that are less than $1.00." /></p>
        </blockquote>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Delivery</strong> - Select either an email or text message delivery.</li>
      <li><strong>To</strong> - Enter a recipent‚Äôs email address or phone number, depending on the previous option. The destination can be your own email box or cellphone.
        <blockquote>
          <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> If the email addressed entered here is the same as the address associated with the purchasing account, a suggestion to reload the card will appear.<br />
 <img src="emailSelf.png" alt="Reloading the card is done from the Gift Card Hyb." /></p>
        </blockquote>
      </li>
      <li><strong>From</strong> and <strong>Message</strong> - These fields allow you to share your name and a message to the gift recipent.</li>
      <li><strong>Quantity</strong> - Select the number of gift cards of the selected value to send at once. This will be reflected in the price instantly
 <img src="cartvalue.png" alt="The cart value multiplies per the quantity." /></li>
      <li><strong>Delivery Date</strong> - Select when to deliver the digital card. The default is immediately.
 <img src="selectAdate.png" alt="A calendar pops up to select a date to send the card." /></li>
      <li><strong>Complete Transaction</strong> - Either add the card(s) to your cart or select Buy It Now to immediately purchase the card with your default payment method. For more information on completing the purchase, see the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html/ref=help_search_1-1?ie=UTF8&amp;nodeId=201889290&amp;qid=1611635317&amp;sr=1-1" target="_blank"><strong>Proceed to Checkout</strong></a> topic in the Amazon Help Documentation.</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>Once purchased and shipped, the gift card is ready for redemption by the recipent. See the <strong>Redeeming and Using an Amazon Gift Card</strong> section for more information on the next steps of this process.</p>
